# Project Context

This is a static website portfolio hosted on Vercel.

## Project Type
- **Static Site**: No build process required
- **Hosting**: Vercel (static file serving)
- **Framework**: None - pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript

## Project Structure
- `index.html` - Portfolio homepage (served at `/`); featured work links, about copy
- `work/<project>/index.html` - Shipped case-study dashboards (Paris, London, …); self-contained HTML with embedded JS data
- `work/nairobi-boutique-fitness-2025/` - Nairobi dashboard exists in repo but project is on hold; `vercel.json` redirects those URLs to `/`; keep local data/scripts if useful
- `scripts/*.html` - Pricing dashboard, `dashboard.html`, `visual*.html`, prototypes; not all linked from `index.html`
- `scripts/*.mjs` - Data pipelines (ClassPass, Google, WHOIS, consolidate; city-specific variants)
- `studio-grow-workbook/` - One-off demo mini-site (`npm run dev`); not core portfolio
- `data/reference/` - Committed reference data; `data/raw/` and `data/processed/` largely gitignored
- `vercel.json` - Vercel configuration (redirects, static output)

## Key Technologies
- **Visualization**: Chart.js, Leaflet.js (loaded via CDN)
- **Styling**: Inline CSS in HTML files
- **Shipped dashboards**: Data hardcoded in the relevant `work/.../index.html` (or specific `scripts/*.html`); no runtime JSON fetch for production dashboards

## Deployment Notes
- All dependencies are loaded from CDNs (no npm packages needed for runtime)
- Large data files are gitignored and not deployed
- Vercel serves files from the repository root

## Development
- No build step required for the portfolio
- Edit HTML files directly; use a simple HTTP server from repo root for correct paths
- For enrichment scripts: Node.js, `.env` / `.env.local` for API keys (gitignored)
